SIMPLE: pelvic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pelvic
<hw>Pel"vic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
in the region of, the pelvis; <as>as, <ex>pelvic</ex>
cellulitis</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Pelvic arch</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Pelvic
girdle</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>the two or more bony or
cartilaginous pieces of the vertebrate skeleton to which the hind limbs
are articulated. When fully ossified, the arch usually consists of three
principal bones on each side, the ilium, ischium, and pubis, which are
often closely united in the adult, forming the innominate bone. See
<cref>Innominate bone</cref>, under <er>Innominate</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pelvimeter</ent>⟦br⟧
